{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013U8iiabwxm8gG15vDsjbNw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster is experiencing a master-not-discovered exception. This makes sense because when we scaled down from 3 to 1 node, Elasticsearch lost quorum for master election. The `es-cluster-0` pod is still running but Elasticsearch's internal cluster is having trouble. Let me check if the ES node is actually healthy first, and then check what's happening with the master election.\n\nIn Elasticsearch 7.x and 8.x, when you have a 3-node cluster and scale down to 1 node, the node needs to reform the cluster with itself as the sole member. The issue is that the cluster state still expects quorum from 3 nodes.\nI need to look at the cluster state and potentially adjust the discovery settings to let it form as a single-node cluster. The `minimum_master_nodes` setting could be the culprit if they're running ES 7.x, though ES 8.x handles this automatically through voting configurations. Let me check what version they're on and examine the current configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":831,"cache_read_input_tokens":36261,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":831},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e6b5e15-9144-4979-91e2-ee21b2fe2b3b","uuid":"400210bb-68f9-4bb6-94d8-1841a86f2d40","request_id":"req_011CcMcieorCzwsirLGxXEzP"}
