{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DVfwA9KaKniukRBTG5LHiv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's Elasticsearch 7.17.9. This means we're using the 7.x API. In ES 7.x, when you scale down from 3 to 1 node, the master election can be disrupted because the \"voting configuration\" still includes the removed nodes. \n\nIn ES 7.x+, we can use the voting exclusions API to handle this. Let me try:\n\n1. `POST /_cluster/voting_config_exclusions?node_names=es-cluster-1,es-cluster-2` - This will tell ES to remove these nodes from the voting configuration\n2. But the nodes are already gone, so the cluster is stuck waiting for nodes that don't exist. I need to check the StatefulSet configuration to see what discovery settings are configured, especially whether it's set up for single-node mode with `discovery.type: single-node` or if it needs proper cluster bootstrap settings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":553,"cache_read_input_tokens":37092,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":553},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e6b5e15-9144-4979-91e2-ee21b2fe2b3b","uuid":"63f5e649-1769-4c15-9f57-68b9b3dd5527","request_id":"req_011CcMcjoH7MK7bwFHWFPTpK"}
